edu.illinois.cs.cogcomp.core.datastructures.textannotation

Class TreeView

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.illinois.cs.cogcomp.core.datastructures.textannotation.View
      • edu.illinois.cs.cogcomp.core.datastructures.textannotation.TreeView
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IQueryable<Constituent>, Serializable, Iterable<Constituent>

    public class TreeView
extends View
    This view represents a tree structure. Use this for parse trees and dependency trees. It extends View by providing functions to get and set Tree objects.
    Author:
    Vivek Srikumar

      • setParseTree

        public void setParseTree(int sentenceId,
                         Tree<String> tree)
        Set the parse tree of the sentenceIdth sentence.

        Note: The same TreeView cannot contain both the parse tree and the dependency tree and will throw an exception if an attempt is made to set the parse tree in a view that has a dependency tree.

      • setDependencyTree

        public void setDependencyTree(int sentenceId,
                              Tree<Pair<String,Integer>> depTree)
        Set the dependency tree of hte sentenceIdth sentence. Each node in the dependency tree specifies both the token and its position with respect to the start of the sentence, not the entire TextAnnotation.

        Note: The same TreeView cannot contain both the parse tree and the dependency tree and will throw an exception if an attempt is made to set the dependency tree of a view that has a phrase-structure tree.

      • setDependencyTree

        public void setDependencyTree(int sentenceId,
                              Tree<Pair<String,Integer>> depTree,
                              double treeScore)
        Set the dependency tree for a specified sentence. Each node in the dependency tree specifies both the token and its position with respect to the start of the sentence, not the entire TextAnnotation.

        Note: The same TreeView cannot contain both the parse tree and the dependency tree and will throw an exception if an attempt is made to set the dependency tree of a view that has a phrase-structure tree.

      • getParsePhrase

        public Constituent getParsePhrase(Constituent c)
                           throws Exception
        Finds the highest node in the parse tree that contains the input constituent. This function is a useful mechanism to get a node from the parse tree. Note that several parse helper functions (such as path helpers) require nodes from the parse view and this function could be used to get them.
        Parameters:
        c - The input constituent. This could be from any view.
        Throws:
        Exception
